Subject: Re: [T2] NGK plug for FI bus?

On Dec 4, 2004, at 11:41 AM, Joseph Broach wrote:

> I just spent some time in the archives, and, as usual, am now totally 
> confused.  I want to get some NGK plugs that will play nice with my 
> new CHT sender, but, which ones?  I've seen recommended (for winter):
>
> BPR5ES
> BR5ES
> B5ES
>
> R=resistor, when would one not want a resistor plug?

The resistor is already in the rotor, and there is resistance in the 
wires.  I don't think you need/want a resistor plug.

> P="projected," what does this mean?

That it sticks out a bit further into the combustion chamber, I think.

I'm installing B6ES plugs in my '76 FI Bus.

